 Sure, here's the API call for booking a second class seat on a Metropolitan Railways train:

curl -X POST \
  https://api.railway.gov/book-ticket \
  headers: {
    "Authorization": "Bearer YOUR_API_KEY",
    "Content-Type": "application/json"
  } \
  body: {
    " passenger": {
      "adult": 1,
      "child": 0,
      "infant": 0
    },
    "journey": {
      "departure": "East City Station",
      "arrival": "Central Business District",
      "departure_time": "08:00:00",
      "return_time": null,
      "class": "second"
    },
    "booking_details": {
      "name": "John Doe",
      "email": "johndoe@example.com",
      "phone": "1234567890"
    }
  }

Replace `YOUR_API_KEY` with your actual API key, and make sure to format the request body according to the API documentation.

This API call will book a second class seat on a Metropolitan Railways train for a single passenger, departing from East City Station at 8:00 AM on a Monday, and arriving at Central Business District. The passenger's name, email, and phone number will be included in the booking details.

Once the API call is successful, you will receive a response with the booking details and a unique booking reference number. You can use this reference number to retrieve your booking details or cancel your booking.

